ExponentialBackoff - Class in org.whispercomm.c2dm4j.backoff
Implementation of Backoff in which the backoff duration increases exponentially in the consecutive failure count.
ExponentialBackoff() - Constructor for class org.whispercomm.c2dm4j.backoff.ExponentialBackoff
Constructs a new backoff with a minimum backoff duration of 1 millisecond and a maximum duration of about about 17.5 minutes.
ExponentialBackoff(float, int) - Constructor for class org.whispercomm.c2dm4j.backoff.ExponentialBackoff
Constructs a new backoff with whose delay duration is computed as follows:
scale * Math.pow(2, min(count, maxCount)) - 1.0)
where count is the number of consecutive failures.

ExponentialBackoff.Provider(float, int) - Constructor for class org.whispercomm.c2dm4j.backoff.ExponentialBackoff.Provider
Constructs a provider that builds backoff instances whose delay durations are computed as follows:
scale * Math.pow(2, min(count, maxCount)) - 1.0)
